FBIS4-25400 "drchi112_d_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-112 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 Northeast Asia Jimmy Carter To Visit DPRK, ROK Jimmy Carter To Visit DPRK, ROK OW1006031094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0256 GMT 10 Jun 94 OW1006031094 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Washington, June 9 (XINHUA) -- Former U.S. President Jimmy Carter said today he and his wife will visit the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) and Republic of Korea (ROK) next week, according to a report reaching here from Atlanta. During the visits, he hopes to discuss "some of the important issues of the day with leaders in the area," Carter said in a statement. "As is the case with other international issues since leaving the White House, I have attempted to stay adequately briefed on the Korean situation," he said. Carter noted that the initiative for his visit has been from Korea, not from Washington. "I will have no official status relating to the U.S. Government," he added.
